label.value: immunoglobulin production involved in immunoglobulin-mediated immune response

value.value: The appearance of immunoglobulin due to biosynthesis or secretion following a cellular stimulus during an immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: hepatic immune response

value.value: An immune response taking place in the liver.

label.value: mucosal immune response

value.value: An immune response taking place in mucosal tissues, including those of the intestinal tract, nasal and upper respiratory tract, and genital tract.

label.value: immune response in gut-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Immune response taking place in the gut-associated lymphoid tissue (GALT). GALT includes Peyer's patches, appendix, and solitary lymph nodules.

label.value: immune response in Peyer's patch

value.value: Immune response taking place in the Peyer's patch, nodular lymphoid structures on the serosal surface of the small intestine.

label.value: tolerance induction in Peyer's patch

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the Peyer's patches.

label.value: tolerance induction in gut-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the gut-associated lymphoid tissue (GALT).

label.value: immune response in nasopharyngeal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: An immune response taking place in the nasopharyngeal-associated lymphoid tissue (NALT). NALT includes the tonsils and adenoids.

label.value: MHC protein complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC protein complex.

label.value: MHC class II protein complex assembly

value.value: The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form an MHC class II protein complex.

label.value: tolerance induction in nasopharyngeal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the nasopharyngeal-associated lymphoid tissue (NALT).

label.value: tolerance induction in mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue (MALT).

label.value: B cell tolerance induction in mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue (MALT) mediated by B cells.

label.value: T cell tolerance induction in mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue (MALT) mediated by T cells.

label.value: dendritic cell chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a dendritic cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: myeloid dendritic cell chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a myeloid dendritic cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: Langerhans cell chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a Langerhans cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: plasmacytoid dendritic cell chemotaxis

value.value: The movement of a plasmacytoid dendritic cell in response to an external stimulus.

label.value: mucosal tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction taking place in the mucosal tissues.

label.value: granuloma formation

value.value: The formation of nodular inflammatory lesions, usually small or granular, firm, persistent, well-structured, and containing compactly grouped T lymphocytes and modified phagocytes such as epithelioid cells, giant cells, and other macrophages. Granuloma formation represents a chronic inflammatory response initiated by various infectious and noninfectious agents. The center of a granuloma consists of fused macrophages, which can become necrotic.

label.value: production of molecular mediator of immune response

value.value: The synthesis or release of any molecular mediator of the immune response, resulting in an increase in its intracellular or extracellular levels.

definition.value: Note that this term is in the subset of terms that should not be used for direct gene product annotation. Instead, select one of the 'regulation' children terms.

label.value: histamine secretion involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The regulated release of histamine by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.

label.value: serotonin secretion involved in inflammatory response

value.value: The regulated release of serotonin by a cell as part of an inflammatory response.

label.value: leukocyte mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a leukocyte.

label.value: myeloid leukocyte mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a myeloid leukocyte.

label.value: neutrophil mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a neutrophil.

label.value: eosinophil mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by an eosinophil.

label.value: mast cell mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a mast cell.

label.value: lymphocyte mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a lymphocyte.

label.value: B cell antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a B cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: peripheral B cell tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction of mature B cells in the peripheral lymphoid tissues: the blood, lymph nodes, spleen, and mucosal-associated lymphoid tissue.

label.value: T cell mediated immunity

value.value: Any process involved in the carrying out of an immune response by a T cell.

label.value: T cell antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a T cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: peripheral T cell tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction of T cells in the periphery, in this case, any location in the body other than the thymus.

label.value: adaptive immune response based on somatic recombination of immune receptors built from immunoglobulin superfamily domains

value.value: An immune response mediated by lymphocytes expressing specific receptors for antigen produced through a somatic diversification process that includes somatic recombination of germline gene segments encoding immunoglobulin superfamily domains. Recombined receptors for antigen encoded by immunoglobulin superfamily domains include T cell receptors and immunoglobulins (antibodies) produced by B cells. The first encounter with antigen elicits a primary immune response that is slow and not of great magnitude. T and B cells selected by antigen become activated and undergo clonal expansion. A fraction of antigen-reactive T and B cells become memory cells, whereas others differentiate into effector cells. The memory cells generated during the primary response enable a much faster and stronger secondary immune response upon subsequent exposures to the same antigen (immunological memory). An example of this is the adaptive immune response found in Mus musculus.

label.value: tolerance induction dependent upon immune response

value.value: Tolerance induction dependent upon an immune response, typically a response by a mature T or B cell in the periphery resulting tolerance towards an antigen via induction of anergy, cellular deletion, or regulatory T cell activation.

label.value: tolerance induction to nonself antigen

value.value: Tolerance induction in response to nonself antigens.

label.value: peripheral tolerance induction

value.value: Tolerance induction in the peripheral lymphoid tissues: blood, lymph nodes, spleen, and mucosal-associated lymphoid tissues.

label.value: germinal center formation

value.value: The process in which germinal centers form. A germinal center is a specialized microenvironment formed when activated B cells enter lymphoid follicles. Germinal centers are the foci for B cell proliferation and somatic hypermutation.

label.value: dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a dendritic cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: myeloid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a myeloid dendritic cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: plasmacytoid dendritic cell antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a plasmacytoid dendritic cell expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: monocyte antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a monocyte expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: macrophage antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The process in which a macrophage expresses antigen (peptide or lipid) on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex.

label.value: antigen processing and presentation of peptide antigen via MHC class I

value.value: The process in which an antigen-presenting cell expresses a peptide antigen on its cell surface in association with an MHC class I protein complex. Class I here refers to classical class I molecules.

label.value: antigen processing and presentation of exogenous peptide antigen

value.value: The process in which an antigen-presenting cell expresses a peptide antigen of exogenous origin on its cell surface in association with an MHC protein complex. The peptide is typically a fragment of a larger exogenous protein which has been degraded within the cell.

label.value: antigen processing and presentation of peptide antigen via MHC class II

value.value: The process in which an antigen-presenting cell expresses a peptide antigen on its cell surface in association with an MHC class II protein complex. The peptide antigen is typically, but not always, processed from a whole protein.

label.value: proteolysis associated with antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The hydrolysis of a peptide bond or bonds within a protein contributing to antigen processing and presentation.

label.value: proteolysis within lysosome associated with antigen processing and presentation

value.value: The hydrolysis of a peptide bond or bonds within a protein by lysosomal resident proteases contributing to antigen processing and presentation.

label.value: antigen processing and presentation of peptide or polysaccharide antigen via MHC class II

value.value: The process in which an antigen-presenting cell expresses antigen (peptide or polysaccharide) on its cell surface in association with an MHC class II protein complex.
